"We have observed the field covering the WXM error box of
GRB040706(HETE trigger 3399; trigger time 11:29:57 UT,and was
 commented as 'Possible SGR') with the
 unfiltered CCD camera on the 30-cm telescope at University of
 Miyazaki.The observation was started 11:41:11 UT on July.06. 
Observed field of view is 43 arcmin centerd on (18h 07m 55s -20d 33' 02").
We have compared our images with the USNO A2.0 catalog . Preliminary analysis
 shows there is no new source brighter than  16.8 mag.
 in the WXM error box reported by HETE.  "

